{"lemma":"أُجُمِ","slug":"أُجُمِ","root":"#.ج.م","root_slug":"_-ج-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ج-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n312","n313","n314","n315","n6215","n6237"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jungle","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a thicket or copse","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dense vegetation which covers the forest floor and may obstruct passage, brushwood, underbrush","tags":["singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed into West Semitic from Akkadian 𒀀𒂵𒈬𒌝 (agammum), from Sumerian 𒀀𒂵𒄠 (agam). Compare Classical Syriac ܐܓܡܐ (ʾaḡmā, “marsh, swamp”) and Hebrew אֲגַם (ʾaḡamm, “lake, swamp”)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.d͡ʒa.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n312","headword_ar":"اَجْمٌ","root":"Ajm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any square, roofed, house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) mentioned by ISd as on the authority of Yaakoob: but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujumN","text_ar":"اُجُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explained by J [in the S] on the same authority. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n313","headword_ar":"اُجْمٌ","root":"Ajm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujumN","text_ar":"اُجُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  It is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajamapN","text_ar":"اَجَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n314","headword_ar":"اَجَمٌ","root":"Ajm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajamapN","text_ar":"اَجَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n315","headword_ar":"اُجُمٌ","root":"Ajm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fortress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uTumN","text_ar":"اُطُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jaAmN","text_ar":"ا=جَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ujumu","text_ar":"الاُجُمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is the name of]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fortress"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in El-Medeeneh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"built of stones by the people of that city:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and Yaakoob says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujumN","text_ar":"اُجُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any square, roofed, house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Sgh.) Imra-el-Keys says, [describing a vehement rain,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"watayomaA='a lamo yatoruko bihaA ji*oEa naxolapK\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA A^ujum~aA A_il~aA ma$iydFA bijanodali"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And Teymà,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a town so called,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it left not therein a trunk of a palm-tree, nor a square, roofed, house, unless raised high with stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in the Calc. ed. of the Mo' allakát, (p. 54,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujum~aA","text_ar":"اُجُمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uTum~aA","text_ar":"اُطُمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has the same meaning]. (S, Sgh.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomN","text_ar":"اَجْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Accord. to As, it is also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujomN","text_ar":"اُجْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n6215","headword_ar":"اجمّ","root":"jm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as an intrans. verb: see 1, in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajm~hu","text_ar":"اجمّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the end of the paragraph, in two places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left him unridden, so that he recovered from his fatigue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a horse. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujim~a","text_ar":"اُجِمَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was left unridden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rested him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave him rest."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomimo nafosaka yawomFA A^awo","text_ar":"اَجْمِمْ نَفْسَكَ يَوْمًا اَوْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomayoni","text_ar":"يَوْمَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rest thyself a day, or two days"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And hence, in a trad. respecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarojalap","text_ar":"سَفَرْجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or quince],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tujim~u Alfuw^aAda","text_ar":"تُجِمُّ الفُوَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It rests the heart, and consolidates it, and completes its soundness and liveliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY laA^asotajim~u","text_ar":"اـِنِّى لَاَسْتَجِمُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobiY bi$~aYo'K mina All~ahowi liA^aqowaY bihi EalaY AlHaq~i","text_ar":"قَلْبِى بِشَّىْءٍ مِنَ اللَّهْوِ لِاَقْوَى بِهِ عَلَى الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I relieve my heart with somewhat of diversion, in order that I may become strong thereby for that which is substantial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"solid, not vain"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frivolous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajm~ AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"اجمّ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave the land rest from tilling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bxE","text_ar":"بخع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~ap","text_ar":"جَمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supply of water, that had collected after drawing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th. TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujim~a AlEinabu","text_ar":"اُجِمَّ العِنَبُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The grape-vine had all its branches that were above the ground cut off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6237","headword_ar":"اَجَمُّ","root":"jm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest, in quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~aA='u","text_ar":"جَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlwaHoYu","text_ar":"وَالوَحْىُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajam~u maA kaAna","text_ar":"اَجَمُّ مَا كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad. of Anas, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The revelation being the most that it used to be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.) ―         -b2-  A bone"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN jam~aA='u AlEiZaAmi","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ جَمَّا=ءُ العِظَامِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman having much flesh"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the bones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~aA='u AlmaraAfiqi","text_ar":"جَمَّا=ءُ المَرَافِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman having much flesh on the elbows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as seems to be indicated by J,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no prominence of the elbows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and if so, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~aA='u","text_ar":"جَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a ewe, in a sense explained in what follows]. (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA Aljam~aA='a Algafiyra","text_ar":"جَاوُوا الجَمَّا=ءَ الغَفِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Msb, K,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~aA='a gafiyrFA","text_ar":"جَمَّا=ءَ غَفِيرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gafiyrFA","text_ar":"غَفِيرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~FA","text_ar":"جَمًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algafiyra","text_ar":"الغَفِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljam~a","text_ar":"الجَمَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came all together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high and low, none of them remaining behind, and they being many:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gfr","text_ar":"غفر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gfr","text_ar":"غفر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hornless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a ram (Mgh, Msb, K) or he-goat; (Msb;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jam~aA='u","text_ar":"جَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a ewe (S, Mgh, Msb) or she-goat: (S, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~N","text_ar":"جُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,] (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no spear"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in war"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) pl. as above. (TA.) The pl. is also applied to horses, (S,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose owners have no spears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the spears being regarded as the horses' horns. (Ham, p. 90.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  A building"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acroterial ornaments such as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uraf","text_ar":"شُرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the pl., (assumed tropical:)  Mosques"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uraf","text_ar":"شُرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon their walls."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  A flat house-top"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no parapet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounding wall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Short; having no elevation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anterior pudendum."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b7-  And, as being likened thereto, or the reverse may be the case, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bowl."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-  Also, the fem., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smooth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b9-  And hence, because of its smoothness, (IAar, TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A helmet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) to which the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gafiyrN","text_ar":"غَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] is applied because it covers the head: but this meaning of “ a helmet ” was not known to ISd on any other authority than that of IAar. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Mgh","Msb","S","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}